{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883092898,"sessionID":"ses_2851eb022ffeUsBkCblQKTFCRz","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae1795d001Na4At8XTkpLVC0","messageID":"msg_d7ae165db001nSB5nY7Xme4ZHK","sessionID":"ses_2851eb022ffeUsBkCblQKTFCRz","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_f27c844450204a4bb77a854a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/ci-cd/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/ci-cd/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # CI/CD Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Automate validation on pull requests (build, lint, tests, codegen drift checks), publish container images on pushes to `main` and version tags, run end-to-end tests on Kind, exercise the Python SDK, and enforce spelling and copyright consistency.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Pull request build verification\n9: The system SHALL build the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Docker build in CI\n12: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n13: - **WHEN** the “Agentcube CI Workflow” job runs\n14: - **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository, set up Docker Buildx, verify `docker`/`buildx` versions, and run `make docker-build`\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Go lint on changed Go code\n17: The system SHALL run `make lint` (golangci-lint) when Go-related paths change on pull requests to `main` or `release-*`.\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Path-filtered lint\n20: - **GIVEN** a pull request and path filter matches `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, or `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n21: - **WHEN** the Lint workflow runs\n22: - **THEN** it SHALL use Go `1.24` and execute `make lint`\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Code generation check\n25: The system SHALL verify generated artifacts match `make gen-all` when API, hack, workflow, or Makefile inputs change.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Regenerate and diff\n28: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, or `Makefile`\n29: - **WHEN** the Codegen Check workflow runs with Go `1.24.4`\n30: - **THEN** it SHALL run `make gen-check` (which runs `gen-all` and `git diff --exit-code`)\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Go test coverage reporting\n33: The system SHALL run race-enabled coverage tests on `pkg/...` for qualifying pull requests and merge groups, optionally uploading to Codecov.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Coverage command\n36: - **GIVEN** path filter `coverage` matches (broad glob excluding some media/docs per workflow)\n37: - **WHEN** the Test Coverage job runs with Go `1.24`\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...` and upload `coverage.out` as an artifact\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: E2E testing on Kind\n41: The system SHALL run `make e2e` in CI using a Kind-capable Ubuntu runner, capturing logs on failure.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: E2E job lifecycle\n44: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n45: - **WHEN** the E2E workflow runs\n46: - **THEN** it SHALL set `ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`, install Kind tool `v0.30.0` (`install_only: true`), run `make e2e` with Go `1.23`, upload `e2e-logs` on failure, and always run `make e2e-clean`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: Python SDK unit tests\n49: The system SHALL run pytest for the SDK when `sdk-python/**` changes.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Editable install and pytest\n52: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `sdk-python/**`\n53: - **WHEN** the Python SDK Tests job runs with Python `3.12` in `sdk-python/`\n54: - **THEN** it SHALL `pip install pytest`, `pip install -e .`, and run `python -m pytest tests/ -v`\n55: \n56: ### Requirement: Python lint\n57: The system SHALL run Ruff from repository root using `pyproject.toml` when Python-touching paths change.\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: Ruff check\n60: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, or the workflow file\n61: - **WHEN** the Python Lint job runs with Python `3.10`\n62: - **THEN** it SHALL `pip install ruff` and run `python3 -m ruff check . --config pyproject.toml`\n63: \n64: ### Requirement: Spelling check (codespell)\n65: The system SHALL run codespell on the repository for pull requests to `main` or `release-*`, temporarily moving files that cause false positives.\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Codespell invocation\n68: - **GIVEN** checkout complete\n69: - **WHEN** codespell runs after backup/remove of `pyproject.toml`, `package-lock.json`, `package.json` at repo root (and nested copies per `find`)\n70: - **THEN** it SHALL use `pip install codespell` and run codespell with `--check-filenames`, specified `--skip` globs, and `--ignore-words-list fo,nam,te,notin,NotIn` on `.`, then restore backed-up files\n71: \n72: ### Requirement: Copyright header check\n73: The system SHALL ensure `make gen-copyright` produces no git diff when applicable files change.\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Copyright workflow\n76: - **GIVEN** path filter marks `copyright` (all paths minus exclusions for md/svg/png/docs/.github per workflow)\n77: - **WHEN** the job runs\n78: - **THEN** it SHALL install `moreutils` (`sponge`), run `make gen-copyright`, and `git diff --exit-code`\n79: \n80: ### Requirement: Release image publication\n81: The system SHALL build and push multi-architecture images for workloadmanager, router, and picod to GitHub Container Registry on pushes to `main` and on semantic version tags.\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Tag selects image tag\n84: - **GIVEN** a `push` event\n85: - **WHEN** `github.ref_type` is `tag`, environment `TAG` SHALL be `github.ref_name`; otherwise `TAG` SHALL be `latest`\n86: - **THEN** the job SHALL log in to `ghcr.io` with `GITHUB_TOKEN` and run `make docker-buildx-push*`, setting `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` and per-image `*_IMAGE=<name>:${TAG}`\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Workflow approval for first-time contributors\n89: The system SHALL optionally approve pending workflow runs for pull requests from repeat contributors or those labeled `ok-to-test`.\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Approve action_required runs\n92: - **GIVEN** `pull_request_target` on `main` or `release-**` with label/sync events\n93: - **WHEN** the contributor is not first-time (more than one PR) or PR has `ok-to-test`\n94: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL list workflow runs for the head SHA with `status: action_required` and call `approveWorkflowRun` for each\n\n(End of file - total 94 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# CI/CD Specification\n\n## Purpose\nAutomate validation on pull requests (build, lint, tests, codegen drift checks), publish container images on pushes to `main` and version tags, run end-to-end tests on Kind, exercise the Python SDK, and enforce spelling and copyright consistency.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Pull request build verification\nThe system SHALL build the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.\n\n#### Scenario: Docker build in CI\n- **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n- **WHEN** the “Agentcube CI Workflow” job runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository, set up Docker Buildx, verify `docker`/`buildx` versions, and run `make docker-build`\n\n### Requirement: Go lint on changed Go code\nThe system SHALL run `make lint` (golangci-lint) when Go-related paths change on pull requests to `main` or `release-*`.\n\n#### Scenario: Path-filtered lint\n- **GIVEN** a pull request and path filter matches `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, or `.github/workflows/lint.yml`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/ci-cd/spec.md","time":{"start":1775883092871,"end":1775883092896}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883092901,"sessionID":"ses_2851eb022ffeUsBkCblQKTFCRz","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae17e6d001c6Na0Lx22UdAeA","messageID":"msg_d7ae165db001nSB5nY7Xme4ZHK","sessionID":"ses_2851eb022ffeUsBkCblQKTFCRz","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_347d76b897484b71b86a2c4a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/ci-cd/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/ci-cd/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube CI/CD — Design\n2: \n3: Sources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/.github/workflows/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/test/`, and (for Make targets) `/tmp/agentcube-ref/Makefile`.\n4: \n5: ## GitHub Actions workflows (summary table)\n6: \n7: | Filename | Workflow `name` | Trigger events | Path filters (dorny/paths-filter or notes) | Jobs | Key steps | Env vars (job/step) | Secrets |\n8: |----------|-----------------|----------------|---------------------------------------------|------|-----------|---------------------|---------|\n9: | `main.yml` | Agentcube CI Workflow | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `build` | Checkout; Docker Buildx setup; verify Docker; `make docker-build` | — | — |\n10: | `e2e.yml` | Agentcube E2E Tests | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `e2e-test` | Checkout; Go 1.23; `helm/kind-action@v1` **install_only** Kind v0.30.0, `cluster_name: agentcube-e2e`; `export ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`; `make e2e`; on failure upload `e2e-logs/`; `always` → `make e2e-clean` | `ARTIFACTS_PATH` (shell) | — |\n11: | `lint.yml` | Lint | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `lint`: `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | `golangci` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24; `make lint` | — | — |\n12: | `python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK Tests | `pull_request`, `merge_group` | `sdk`: `sdk-python/**` | `python-sdk-tests` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.12 in `sdk-python/`; `pip install pytest`; `pip install -e .`; `python -m pytest tests/ -v` | Default `working-directory: sdk-python` | — |\n13: | `python-lint.yml` | Python Lint | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `python`: `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, workflow self | `python_lint` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.10; `pip install ruff`; `ruff check . --config pyproject.toml` | — | — |\n14: | `test-coverage.yml` | Test Coverage | `pull_request`, `merge_group`, `workflow_call` | `coverage`: `**` minus `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png` | `coverage` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: free disk space; Go 1.24; `go test` with coverage; step summary; Codecov upload; artifact `go-coverage` | `CODECOV_TOKEN` passed to Codecov action when present | `secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN` (optional; declared for `workflow_call`) |\n15: | `codegen-check.yml` | Codegen Check | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `codegen`: `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile` | `codegen-check` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24.4; `make gen-check` | — | — |\n16: | `copyright-check.yml` | Copyright Check | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `copyright`: all files except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**` | `build` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: `apt install moreutils`; `make gen-copyright`; `git diff --exit-code` | — | — |\n17: | `codespell.yml` | Codespell | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none — scans tree after temporarily removing some manifests)* | `codespell` | Backup/remove `pyproject.toml`, `package.json`, `package-lock.json`; `pip install codespell`; `codespell` with `--check-filenames`, `--skip`, `--ignore-words-list`; restore files | — | — |\n18: | `build-push-release.yml` | Build and Push Release Images | `push` → `main`; `push` tags `v*.*.*`, `v*.*.*-*` | *(none)* | `build-and-push` | Checkout; Go 1.24.4; Buildx; `docker/login-action` to `ghcr.io`; set `TAG` from ref; `make docker-buildx-push` (workload manager), `docker-buildx-push-router`, `docker-buildx-push-picod` with `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `TAG`, `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` | `GITHUB_TOKEN` (registry login) |\n19: | `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify Plugin Publish | `push` tags `dify-plugin/v*` | *(none)* | `publish` | Download `dify-plugin` CLI 0.0.6; install `yq`; read `manifest.yaml`; package plugin; checkout `author/dify-plugins` with token; move `.difypkg`; branch, commit, push; `gh pr create` to `langgenius/dify-plugins` | `GH_TOKEN` on PR step | `PLUGIN_ACTION` (repo checkout + `gh`; cross-repo PR) |\n20: | `workflows-approve.yml` | Approve Workflows | `pull_request_target` types `labeled`, `synchronize` → `main`, `release-**` | *(logic: first-time contributor vs `ok-to-test` label)* | `approve` | `github-script`: list contributor PRs; if not first-time or has `ok-to-test`, list `action_required` workflow runs for SHA and approve | — | `GITHUB_TOKEN` |\n21: \n22: ### Workflow notes\n23: \n24: - **`e2e.yml`**: Uses Kind action with `install_only: true` so the cluster is created by `run_e2e.sh` (`kind create cluster`), avoiding double-creation.\n25: - **`test-coverage.yml`**: `workflow_call` declares `CODECOV_TOKEN` optional for reusable invocation; PR runs use the repo secret when configured.\n26: - **`build-push-release.yml`**: Uses older action major versions (`checkout@v3`, `setup-go@v4`, `buildx@v2`) than most other workflows.\n27: \n28: ---\n29: \n30: ## E2E test setup (`test/e2e/run_e2e.sh`)\n31: \n32: ### Kind cluster\n33: \n34: | Item | Value / behavior |\n35: |------|------------------|\n36: | Default cluster name | `E2E_CLUSTER_NAME` → `agentcube-e2e` |\n37: | Creation | `kind create cluster --name \"${E2E_CLUSTER_NAME}\"` if missing; if exists and `E2E_CLEAN_CLUSTER=true` (default), delete then recreate |\n38: | CI alignment | `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` installs Kind **v0.30.0** via `helm/kind-action@v1` (`install_only: true`) |\n39: | Skip setup | `E2E_SKIP_SETUP=true` skips `run_setup` and assumes an existing cluster |\n40: \n41: ### CRD / agent-sandbox installation\n42: \n43: Applied via `kubectl apply --validate=false` after downloading release assets (URLs built from `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION`, default **`v0.1.1`**):\n44: \n45: 1. `https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox/releases/download/${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}/manifest.yaml`\n46: 2. `https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox/releases/download/${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}/extensions.yaml`\n47: \n48: ### Images pre-pulled and loaded into Kind\n49: \n50: - `registry.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/agent-sandbox-controller:${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}`\n51: - `python:3.9-slim` (echo agent workload)\n52: \n53: Local images built and loaded:\n54: \n55: - `make docker-build` → default `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE` **`workloadmanager:latest`**\n56: - `make docker-build-router` → **`agentcube-router:latest`**\n57: - `make docker-build-picod` → **`picod:latest`**\n58: - `REDIS_IMAGE` default **`redis:7-alpine`** (Deployment + Service in namespace)\n59: \n60: ### Helm (AgentCube chart)\n61: \n62: | Item | Value |\n63: |------|--------|\n64: | Chart path | `manifests/charts/base` |\n65: | Release / namespace | `agentcube` in `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (default `agentcube`), `--create-namespace` |\n66: | Redis addr | `redis.${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}.svc.cluster.local:6379`, password empty |\n67: | Workload manager image | `repository=workloadmanager`, `tag=latest` |\n68: | Router image | `repository=agentcube-router`, `tag=latest` |\n69: | Router RBAC | `router.rbac.create=true`, `router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router` |\n70: | Extra env (JSON via `--set-json`) | Workload manager: `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`, `JWT_KEY_SECRET_NAMESPACE=agentcube`; Router: `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n71: | Wait | `helm upgrade --install ... --wait` |\n72: \n73: ### Kubernetes fixtures applied during setup\n74: \n75: | Path | Purpose |\n76: |------|---------|\n77: | `test/e2e/echo_agent.yaml` | `AgentRuntime` `echo-agent` in `agentcube` |\n78: | Generated from `echo_agent.yaml` (sed) | `echo-agent-short-ttl` with `sessionTimeout: \"30s\"` for TTL tests |\n79: | `test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter.yaml` | `CodeInterpreter` `e2e-code-interpreter` in `agentcube` |\n80: \n81: Warm-pool Go tests apply `e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml` at runtime (not in initial `kubectl apply` list in the shell script).\n82: \n83: ### Port forwards and health checks\n84: \n85: - Workload manager: `kubectl port-forward svc/workloadmanager` → `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT` (default **8080**) → pod 8080\n86: - Router: `kubectl port-forward svc/agentcube-router` → `ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT` (default **8081**) → pod 8080\n87: - Readiness: `curl` to `http://localhost:${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT}/health` and `http://localhost:${ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT}/health/live`\n88: \n89: ### Auth for tests\n90: \n91: - ServiceAccount `e2e-test` in `agentcube` + `ClusterRoleBinding` to `workloadmanager` clusterrole\n92: - API token: `kubectl create token e2e-test -n agentcube --duration=24h` → `API_TOKEN`\n93: \n94: ### Python venv for E2E\n95: \n96: - Directory: `E2E_VENV_DIR` (default `/tmp/agentcube-e2e-venv`)\n97: - `python3 -m venv`, `pip install -e ./sdk-python`, verify `import agentcube`\n98: \n99: ### Test commands invoked by `run_e2e.sh`\n100: \n101: **Go** (from repository root):\n102: \n103: ```bash\n104: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=\"http://localhost:${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT}\" \\\n105: ROUTER_URL=\"http://localhost:${ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT}\" \\\n106: API_TOKEN=$API_TOKEN \\\n107: go test -v ./test/e2e/...\n108: ```\n109: \n110: **Python** (after `cd` to `test/e2e`):\n111: \n112: ```bash\n113: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=\"...\" ROUTER_URL=\"...\" API_TOKEN=$API_TOKEN \\\n114: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE=\"${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}\" \\\n115: \"$E2E_VENV_DIR/bin/python\" test_codeinterpreter.py\n116: ```\n117: \n118: (`test_codeinterpreter.py` uses `unittest.main()` and appends `--verbose` if missing.)\n119: \n120: ### Failure artifacts\n121: \n122: On test failure, `collect_component_logs` writes under `ARTIFACTS_PATH` (CI: `${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`): workload manager, router, and sandbox pod logs/describes.\n123: \n124: ---\n125: \n126: ## Test directory structure\n127: \n128: ```\n129: test/\n130: ├── OWNERS\n131: └── e2e/\n132:     ├── README.md\n133:     ├── __init__.py\n134:     ├── run_e2e.sh\n135:     ├── e2e_test.go\n136:     ├── test_codeinterpreter.py\n137:     ├── echo_agent.yaml\n138:     ├── e2e_code_interpreter.yaml\n139:     └── e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml\n140: ```\n141: \n142: ### Fixture paths (relative to repo root unless noted)\n143: \n144: | Fixture | Description |\n145: |---------|-------------|\n146: | `test/e2e/echo_agent.yaml` | Echo `AgentRuntime` for router invocation tests |\n147: | `test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter.yaml` | Standard `CodeInterpreter` (`e2e-code-interpreter`, namespace `agentcube`) |\n148: | `test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml` | `CodeInterpreter` with `warmPoolSize: 2` in `default` (loaded by Go tests from **package cwd** as `e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml`) |\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ## Go test commands and flags in CI\n153: \n154: | Workflow / entrypoint | Command | Flags / notes |\n155: |------------------------|---------|----------------|\n156: | `test-coverage.yml` | `go test` | `-race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...` |\n157: | `e2e.yml` via `make e2e` → `run_e2e.sh` | `go test` | `-v ./test/e2e/...` with env `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `API_TOKEN` |\n158: \n159: ---\n160: \n161: ## Python test commands in CI\n162: \n163: | Workflow | Working dir | Command |\n164: |----------|-------------|---------|\n165: | `python-sdk-tests.yml` | `sdk-python` | `python -m pip install --upgrade pip`; `pip install pytest`; `pip install -e .`; `python -m pytest tests/ -v` |\n166: | `e2e.yml` (via `run_e2e.sh`) | Invoked from `test/e2e/` | `\"$E2E_VENV_DIR/bin/python\" test_codeinterpreter.py` (unittest, verbosity 2) |\n167: \n168: ---\n169: \n170: ## Key Make targets referenced by CI\n171: \n172: | Target | Referenced in | Role |\n173: |--------|----------------|------|\n174: | `docker-build` | `main.yml`, `run_e2e.sh` | Build workload manager image |\n175: | `docker-build-router` | `run_e2e.sh` | Build router image |\n176: | `docker-build-picod` | `run_e2e.sh` | Build picod image |\n177: | `docker-buildx-push` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push workload manager image (`IMAGE_REGISTRY`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE=workloadmanager:${TAG}`) |\n178: | `docker-buildx-push-router` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push router image |\n179: | `docker-buildx-push-picod` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push picod image |\n180: | `e2e` | `e2e.yml` | Run `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` |\n181: | `e2e-clean` | `e2e.yml` | `kind delete cluster --name $(E2E_CLUSTER_NAME)`; `rm -rf /tmp/agent-sandbox` |\n182: | `lint` | `lint.yml` | `golangci-lint` (project default) |\n183: | `gen-check` | `codegen-check.yml` | Verify generated code up to date |\n184: | `gen-copyright` | `copyright-check.yml` | Generate copyright headers for check |\n185: \n186: ---\n187: \n188: ## Additional reference: E2E README vs script\n189: \n190: `test/e2e/README.md` states Go **1.24+** and generic “install CRDs and agent-sandbox”; the **CI workflow** pins Go **1.23** for E2E, and **run_e2e.sh** pins **agent-sandbox `v0.1.1`** by default (overridable via `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION`).\n\n(End of file - total 190 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube CI/CD — Design\n\nSources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/.github/workflows/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/test/`, and (for Make targets) `/tmp/agentcube-ref/Makefile`.\n\n## GitHub Actions workflows (summary table)\n\n| Filename | Workflow `name` | Trigger events | Path filters (dorny/paths-filter or notes) | Jobs | Key steps | Env vars (job/step) | Secrets |\n|----------|-----------------|----------------|---------------------------------------------|------|-----------|---------------------|---------|\n| `main.yml` | Agentcube CI Workflow | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `build` | Checkout; Docker Buildx setup; verify Docker; `make docker-build` | — | — |\n| `e2e.yml` | Agentcube E2E Tests | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `e2e-test` | Checkout; Go 1.23; `helm/kind-action@v1` **install_only** Kind v0.30.0, `cluster_name: agentcube-e2e`; `export ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`; `make e2e`; on failure upload `e2e-logs/`; `always` → `make e2e-clean` | `ARTIFACTS_PATH` (shell) | — |\n| `lint.yml` | Lint | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `lint`: `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | `golangci` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24; `make lint` | — | — |\n| `python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK Tests | `pull_request`, `merge_group` | `sdk`: `sdk-python/**` | `python-sdk-tests` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.12 in `sdk-python/`; `pip install pytest`; `pip install -e .`; `python -m pytest tests/ -v` | Default `working-directory: sdk-python` | — |\n| `python-lint.yml` | Python Lint | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `python`: `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, workflow self | `python_lint` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.10; `pip install ruff`; `ruff check . --config pyproject.toml` | — | — |\n| `test-coverage.yml` | Test Coverage | `pull_request`, `merge_group`, `workflow_call` | `coverage`: `**` minus `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png` | `coverage` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: free disk space; Go 1.24; `go test` with coverage; step summary; Codecov upload; artifact `go-coverage` | `CODECOV_TOKEN` passed to Codecov action when present | `secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN` (optional; declared for `workflow_call`) |\n| `codegen-check.yml` | Codegen Check | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `codegen`: `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile` | `codegen-check` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24.4; `make gen-check` | — | — |\n| `copyright-check.yml` | Copyright Check | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `copyright`: all files except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**` | `build` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: `apt install moreutils`; `make gen-copyright`; `git diff --exit-code` | — | — |\n| `codespell.yml` | Codespell | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none — scans tree after temporarily removing some manifests)* | `codespell` | Backup/remove `pyproject.toml`, `package.json`, `package-lock.json`; `pip install codespell`; `codespell` with `--check-filenames`, `--skip`, `--ignore-words-list`; restore files | — | — |\n| `build-push-release.yml` | Build and Push Release Images | `push` → `main`; `push` tags `v*.*.*`, `v*.*.*-*` | *(none)* | `build-and-push` | Checkout; Go 1.24.4; Buildx; `docker/login-action` to `ghcr.io`; set `TAG` from ref; `make docker-buildx-push` (workload manager), `docker-buildx-push-router`, `docker-buildx-push-picod` with `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `TAG`, `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` | `GITHUB_TOKEN` (registry login) |\n| `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify Plugin Publish | `push` tags `dify-plugin/v*` | *(none)* | `publish` | Download `dify-plugin` CLI 0.0.6; install `yq`; read `manifest.yaml`; package plugin; checkout `author/dify-plugins` with token; move `.difypkg`; branch, commit, push; `gh pr create` to `langgenius/dify-plugins` | `GH_TOKEN` on PR step | `PLUGIN_ACTION` (repo checkout + `gh`; cross-repo PR) |\n| `workflows-approve.yml` | Approve Workflows | `pull_request_target` types `labeled`, `synchronize` → `main`, `release-**` | *(logic: first-time contributor vs `ok-to-test` label)* | `approve` | `github-script`: list contributor PRs; if not first-time or has `ok-to-test`, list `action_required` workflow runs for SHA and approve | — | `GITHUB_TOKEN` |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/ci-cd/design.md","time":{"start":1775883092876,"end":1775883092899}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883092908,"sessionID":"ses_2851eb022ffeUsBkCblQKTFCRz","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae173be001VGHhv74L4JeBRH","messageID":"msg_d7ae165db001nSB5nY7Xme4ZHK","sessionID":"ses_2851eb022ffeUsBkCblQKTFCRz","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_2e4bd6a3598541b08c736e09","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-033/spec/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-033/spec/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification — AR-033: Makefile 构建目标体系\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **Module:** `root`  \n6: **Language:** Makefile  \n7: **Size:** M  \n8: **Type:** Makefile target system for Docker image build, push, validate, test lifecycle management\n9: \n10: **Base Specs:** design.md, deployment/docker/delta-spec.md (AR-032)\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements & Scenarios\n15: \n16: ### REQ-033.1: Build Targets (docker-build-*)\n17: \n18: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make targets for building Docker images for all components (Workload Manager, Router, Picod).\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Build all images\n21: - **GIVEN** Makefile exists with `docker-build-all` target\n22: - **WHEN** `make docker-build-all` is executed\n23: - **THEN** it SHALL build all three images (workloadmanager, router, picod) sequentially\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Build Workload Manager image\n26: - **GIVEN** `deployment/docker/Dockerfile` exists\n27: - **WHEN** `make docker-build-workloadmanager` is executed\n28: - **THEN** it SHALL build image tagged with `$(DOCKER_TAG)`, `$(COMMIT_SHA)`, and `$(VERSION)`\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Build Router image\n31: - **GIVEN** `deployment/docker/Dockerfile.router` exists\n32: - **WHEN** `make docker-build-router` is executed\n33: - **THEN** it SHALL build image tagged with `$(DOCKER_TAG)`, `$(COMMIT_SHA)`, and `$(VERSION)`\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Build Picod image\n36: - **GIVEN** `deployment/docker/Dockerfile.picod` exists\n37: - **WHEN** `make docker-build-picod` is executed\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL build image tagged with `$(DOCKER_TAG)`, `$(COMMIT_SHA)`, and `$(VERSION)`\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Default registry configuration\n41: - **GIVEN** no `DOCKER_REGISTRY` variable is set\n42: - **WHEN** any build target runs\n43: - **THEN** it SHALL use default registry `ghcr.io/volcano-sh`\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Custom registry override\n46: - **GIVEN** `DOCKER_REGISTRY=registry.example.com` is set\n47: - **WHEN** build target runs\n48: - **THEN** it SHALL use custom registry in image name\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Default tag configuration\n51: - **GIVEN** no `DOCKER_TAG` variable is set\n52: - **WHEN** any build target runs\n53: - **THEN** it SHALL use default tag `latest`\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Custom tag override\n56: - **GIVEN** `DOCKER_TAG=v1.0.0` is set\n57: - **WHEN** build target runs\n58: - **THEN** it SHALL use custom tag in image name\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ### REQ-033.2: Push Targets (docker-push-*)\n63: \n64: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make targets for pushing Docker images to container registry.\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: Push all images\n67: - **GIVEN** images are built and `docker-push-all` target exists\n68: - **WHEN** `make docker-push-all` is executed\n69: - **THEN** it SHALL push all three images to registry\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Push Workload Manager image\n72: - **GIVEN** workloadmanager image is built\n73: - **WHEN** `make docker-push-workloadmanager` is executed\n74: - **THEN** it SHALL push all three tags (latest, commit-sha, version) to registry\n75: \n76: #### Scenario: Push Router image\n77: - **GIVEN** router image is built\n78: - **WHEN** `make docker-push-router` is executed\n79: - **THEN** it SHALL push all three tags (latest, commit-sha, version) to registry\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: Push Picod image\n82: - **GIVEN** picod image is built\n83: - **WHEN** `make docker-push-picod` is executed\n84: - **THEN** it SHALL push all three tags (latest, commit-sha, version) to registry\n85: \n86: #### Scenario: Push with custom registry\n87: - **GIVEN** `DOCKER_REGISTRY=registry.example.com` is set\n88: - **WHEN** push target runs\n89: - **THEN** it SHALL push to specified custom registry\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ### REQ-033.3: Kind Load Targets (kind-load-*)\n94: \n95: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make targets for loading Docker images to local Kind Kubernetes cluster.\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Load all images to Kind\n98: - **GIVEN** Kind cluster is running and images are built\n99: - **WHEN** `make kind-load-all` is executed\n100: - **THEN** it SHALL load all three images to Kind cluster\n101: \n102: #### Scenario: Load Workload Manager image to Kind\n103: - **GIVEN** Kind cluster is running and workloadmanager image is built\n104: - **WHEN** `make kind-load-workloadmanager` is executed\n105: - **THEN** it SHALL load workloadmanager image with `$(DOCKER_TAG)` to Kind\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Load Router image to Kind\n108: - **GIVEN** Kind cluster is running and router image is built\n109: - **WHEN** `make kind-load-router` is executed\n110: - **THEN** it SHALL load router image with `$(DOCKER_TAG)` to Kind\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: Load Picod image to Kind\n113: - **GIVEN** Kind cluster is running and picod image is built\n114: - **WHEN** `make kind-load-picod` is executed\n115: - **THEN** it SHALL load picod image with `$(DOCKER_TAG)` to Kind\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: Kind not installed\n118: - **GIVEN** Kind is not installed on the system\n119: - **WHEN** `make kind-load-all` is executed\n120: - **THEN** it SHALL fail with appropriate error message about Kind not found\n121: \n122: ---\n123: \n124: ### REQ-033.4: Multi-architecture Build Targets (docker-buildx-*)\n125: \n126: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make targets for building multi-architecture Docker images using Docker Buildx.\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Build all multi-arch images\n129: - **GIVEN** Docker Buildx is available and `docker-buildx-all` target exists\n130: - **WHEN** `make docker-buildx-all` is executed\n131: - **THEN** it SHALL build multi-arch images for all three components\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: Build Workload Manager multi-arch image\n134: - **GIVEN** Docker Buildx is available\n135: - **WHEN** `make docker-buildx-workloadmanager` is executed\n136: - **THEN** it SHALL build image for `linux/amd64,linux/arm64` platforms and push to registry\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: Build Router multi-arch image\n139: - **GIVEN** Docker Buildx is available\n140: - **WHEN** `make docker-buildx-router` is executed\n141: - **THEN** it SHALL build image for `linux/amd64,linux/arm64` platforms and push to registry\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: Build Picod multi-arch image\n144: - **GIVEN** Docker Buildx is available\n145: - **WHEN** `make docker-buildx-picod` is executed\n146: - **THEN** it SHALL build image for `linux/amd64,linux/arm64` platforms and push to registry\n147: \n148: #### Scenario: Buildx not available\n149: - **GIVEN** Docker Buildx is not installed\n150: - **WHEN** `make docker-buildx-all` is executed\n151: - **THEN** it SHALL fail with appropriate error message about buildx not found\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ### REQ-033.5: Validate Targets (docker-validate-*)\n156: \n157: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make targets for validating Docker images against quality standards (size, layers, security, ports).\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: Validate all images\n160: - **GIVEN** images are built and `docker-validate` target exists\n161: - **WHEN** `make docker-validate` is executed\n162: - **THEN** it SHALL run validation script against all three images\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: Validate Workload Manager image\n165: - **GIVEN** workloadmanager image is built\n166: - **WHEN** `make docker-validate-workloadmanager` is executed\n167: - **THEN** it SHALL run `deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` against the image\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: Validate Router image\n170: - **GIVEN** router image is built\n171: - **WHEN** `make docker-validate-router` is executed\n172: - **THEN** it SHALL run `deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` against the image\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: Validate Picod image\n175: - **GIVEN** picod image is built\n176: - **WHEN** `make docker-validate-picod` is executed\n177: - **THEN** it SHALL run `deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` against the image\n178: \n179: #### Scenario: Validation script not found\n180: - **GIVEN** `deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` does not exist\n181: - **WHEN** `make docker-validate` is executed\n182: - **THEN** it SHALL fail with appropriate error message about missing script\n183: \n184: ---\n185: \n186: ### REQ-033.6: Test Targets (docker-test-*)\n187: \n188: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make targets for running Docker build and runtime tests.\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: Run all Docker tests\n191: - **GIVEN** `docker-test` target exists\n192: - **WHEN** `make docker-test` is executed\n193: - **THEN** it SHALL run both `docker-test-build` and `docker-test-runtime`\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: Run build tests\n196: - **GIVEN** `docker-test-build` target exists\n197: - **WHEN** `make docker-test-build` is executed\n198: - **THEN** it SHALL run `deployment/docker/test/build_test.sh`\n199: \n200: #### Scenario: Run runtime tests\n201: - **GIVEN** `docker-test-runtime` target exists\n202: - **WHEN** `make docker-test-runtime` is executed\n203: - **THEN** it SHALL run `deployment/docker/test/runtime_test.sh`\n204: \n205: #### Scenario: Test script not found\n206: - **GIVEN** test script does not exist\n207: - **WHEN** corresponding test target is executed\n208: - **THEN** it SHALL fail with appropriate error message about missing script\n209: \n210: ---\n211: \n212: ### REQ-033.7: Clean Target (docker-clean)\n213: \n214: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make target for cleaning up local Docker images.\n215: \n216: #### Scenario: Clean all local images\n217: - **GIVEN** local images exist and `docker-clean` target exists\n218: - **WHEN** `make docker-clean` is executed\n219: - **THEN** it SHALL remove all local tags for workloadmanager, router, and picod images\n220: \n221: #### Scenario: Clean with missing images\n222: - **GIVEN** some images do not exist locally\n223: - **WHEN** `make docker-clean` is executed\n224: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT fail and SHALL silently skip missing images\n225: \n226: ---\n227: \n228: ### REQ-033.8: Help Target (help)\n229: \n230: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `help` target that prints available Make targets and their descriptions.\n231: \n232: #### Scenario: Display help information\n233: - **GIVEN** `help` target exists in Makefile\n234: - **WHEN** `make help` is executed\n235: - **THEN** it SHALL print all available targets grouped by category (build, push, kind, buildx, test, validate, clean)\n236: \n237: #### Scenario: Display variable values\n238: - **GIVEN** `help` target is executed\n239: - **WHEN** help output is printed\n240: - **THEN** it SHALL show current values of `DOCKER_REGISTRY`, `DOCKER_TAG`, `VERSION`, and `COMMIT_SHA`\n241: \n242: ---\n243: \n244: ### REQ-033.9: Validation Script (validate.sh)\n245: \n246: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` script for validating Docker images.\n247: \n248: #### Scenario: Validate image size\n249: - **GIVEN** a Docker image exists\n250: - **WHEN** `validate.sh` runs against the image\n251: - **THEN** it SHALL check that image size is under 50MB\n252: \n253: #### Scenario: Validate layer count\n254: - **GIVEN** a Docker image exists\n255: - **WHEN** `validate.sh` runs\n256: - **THEN** it SHALL check that image has 5 or fewer layers\n257: \n258: #### Scenario: Validate non-root user\n259: - **GIVEN** a Docker image exists\n260: - **WHEN** `validate.sh` runs\n261: - **THEN** it SHALL check that image specifies non-root user (not root)\n262: \n263: #### Scenario: Validate port exposure\n264: - **GIVEN** a Docker image exists\n265: - **WHEN** `validate.sh` runs\n266: - **THEN** it SHALL check that port 8080 is exposed\n267: \n268: #### Scenario: Validate health check\n269: - **GIVEN** a Docker image exists\n270: - **WHEN** `validate.sh` runs\n271: - **THEN** it SHALL check that HEALTHCHECK instruction is configured\n272: \n273: #### Scenario: Image not found\n274: - **GIVEN** the specified image does not exist\n275: - **WHEN** `validate.sh` is executed\n276: - **THEN** it SHALL exit with error code and message \"Image not found\"\n277: \n278: #### Scenario: Script is executable\n279: - **GIVEN** `validate.sh` file exists\n280: - **WHEN** file permissions are checked\n281: - **THEN** it SHALL have execute permission (`chmod +x`)\n282: \n283: ---\n284: \n285: ### REQ-033.10: Build Test Script (build_test.sh)\n286: \n287: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `deployment/docker/test/build_test.sh` script for testing Docker build process.\n288: \n289: #### Scenario: Check Dockerfile existence\n290: - **GIVEN** `build_test.sh` runs\n291: - **WHEN** it checks for Dockerfiles\n292: - **THEN** it SHALL verify `Dockerfile`, `Dockerfile.router`, and `Dockerfile.picod` exist\n293: \n294: #### Scenario: Check Makefile targets\n295: - **GIVEN** `build_test.sh` runs\n296: - **WHEN** it checks Makefile targets\n297: - **THEN** it SHALL verify `docker-build-all` target is available\n298: \n299: #### Scenario: Check Docker daemon\n300: - **GIVEN** `build_test.sh` runs\n301: - **WHEN** it checks Docker daemon\n302: - **THEN** it SHALL verify Docker daemon is running\n303: \n304: #### Scenario: Check buildx availability\n305: - **GIVEN** `build_test.sh` runs\n306: - **WHEN** it checks buildx\n307: - **THEN** it SHALL verify Docker buildx is available (optional, non-fatal)\n308: \n309: #### Scenario: Script is executable\n310: - **GIVEN** `build_test.sh` file exists\n311: - **WHEN** file permissions are checked\n312: - **THEN** it SHALL have execute permission (`chmod +x`)\n313: \n314: ---\n315: \n316: ### REQ-033.11: Runtime Test Script (runtime_test.sh)\n317: \n318: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide `deployment/docker/test/runtime_test.sh` script for testing Docker container runtime behavior.\n319: \n320: #### Scenario: Test container startup\n321: - **GIVEN** `runtime_test.sh` runs and test image exists\n322: - **WHEN** it attempts container startup\n323: - **THEN** it SHALL verify container starts successfully\n324: \n325: #### Scenario: Test health check configuration\n326: - **GIVEN** `runtime_test.sh` runs\n327: - **WHEN** it checks health check\n328: - **THEN** it SHALL verify HEALTHCHECK is configured in image\n329: \n330: #### Scenario: Test port exposure\n331: - **GIVEN** `runtime_test.sh` runs\n332: - **WHEN** it checks ports\n333: - **THEN** it SHALL verify port 8080 is exposed\n334: \n335: #### Scenario: Test non-root user\n336: - **GIVEN** `runtime_test.sh` runs\n337: - **WHEN** it checks user configuration\n338: - **THEN** it SHALL verify container runs as non-root user\n339: \n340: #### Scenario: Image not available\n341: - **GIVEN** test image does not exist locally\n342: - **WHEN** `runtime_test.sh` runs\n343: - **THEN** it SHALL gracefully skip tests with warning messages (non-fatal)\n344: \n345: #### Scenario: Script is executable\n346: - **GIVEN** `runtime_test.sh` file exists\n347: - **WHEN** file permissions are checked\n348: - **THEN** it SHALL have execute permission (`chmod +x`)\n349: \n350: ---\n351: \n352: ### REQ-033.12: Version and Commit Variables\n353: \n354: **Requirement:** The system SHALL automatically derive VERSION and COMMIT_SHA from git for use in image tagging.\n355: \n356: #### Scenario: Derive VERSION from git tags\n357: - **GIVEN** repository has git tags\n358: - **WHEN** Makefile evaluates `VERSION` variable\n359: - **THEN** it SHALL use `git describe --tags --always --dirty` output\n360: \n361: #### Scenario: Fallback VERSION for no tags\n362: - **GIVEN** repository has no git tags\n363: - **WHEN** Makefile evaluates `VERSION` variable\n364: - **THEN** it SHALL fallback to `dev`\n365: \n366: #### Scenario: Derive COMMIT_SHA from git\n367: - **GIVEN** repository is a valid git repo\n368: - **WHEN** Makefile evaluates `COMMIT_SHA` variable\n369: - **THEN** it SHALL use `git rev-parse --short HEAD` output\n370: \n371: #### Scenario: Fallback COMMIT_SHA for non-git\n372: - **GIVEN** not in a git repository\n373: - **WHEN** Makefile evaluates `COMMIT_SHA` variable\n374: - **THEN** it SHALL fallback to `unknown`\n375: \n376: #### Scenario: Override VERSION from environment\n377: - **GIVEN** `VERSION` environment variable is set\n378: - **WHEN** Makefile is invoked\n379: - **THEN** it SHALL use environment variable value\n380: \n381: #### Scenario: Override COMMIT_SHA from environment\n382: - **GIVEN** `COMMIT_SHA` environment variable is set\n383: - **WHEN** Makefile is invoked\n384: - **THEN** it SHALL use environment variable value\n385: \n386: ---\n387: \n388: ### REQ-033.13: Image Name Configuration\n389: \n390: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide consistent image naming convention for all components.\n391: \n392: #### Scenario: Workload Manager image name\n393: - **GIVEN** Makefile is evaluated\n394: - **WHEN** `WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE` variable is expanded\n395: - **THEN** it SHALL equal `$(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/workloadmanager`\n396: \n397: #### Scenario: Router image name\n398: - **GIVEN** Makefile is evaluated\n399: - **WHEN** `ROUTER_IMAGE` variable is expanded\n400: - **THEN** it SHALL equal `$(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/router`\n401: \n402: #### Scenario: Picod image name\n403: - **GIVEN** Makefile is evaluated\n404: - **WHEN** `PICOD_IMAGE` variable is expanded\n405: - **THEN** it SHALL equal `$(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/picod`\n406: \n407: ---\n408: \n409: ### REQ-033.14: PHONY Target Declarations\n410: \n411: **Requirement:** The system SHALL declare all Make targets as `.PHONY` to prevent conflicts with files of the same name.\n412: \n413: #### Scenario: All targets declared as PHONY\n414: - **GIVEN** Makefile exists\n415: - **WHEN** `.PHONY` declarations are inspected\n416: - **THEN** all targets (docker-build-*, docker-push-*, kind-load-*, docker-buildx-*, docker-validate-*, docker-test-*, docker-clean, help) SHALL be declared as `.PHONY`\n417: \n418: ---\n419: \n420: ### REQ-033.15: Error Handling\n421: \n422: **Requirement:** The system SHALL handle errors gracefully in Make targets and scripts.\n423: \n424: #### Scenario: Docker command failure\n425: - **GIVEN** Docker daemon is not running\n426: - **WHEN** a build target is executed\n427: - **THEN** it SHALL fail with clear error message about Docker not being available\n428: \n429: #### Scenario: Clean target with missing images\n430: - **GIVEN** some images do not exist\n431: - **WHEN** `make docker-clean` runs\n432: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT fail (uses `-` prefix to ignore errors)\n433: \n434: #### Scenario: Missing Dockerfile\n435: - **GIVEN** Dockerfile does not exist\n436: - **WHEN** build target runs\n437: - **THEN** Docker build command SHALL fail with appropriate error\n438: \n439: ---\n440: \n441: ## Data Types\n442: \n443: ```makefile\n444: # Makefile variables\n445: DOCKER_REGISTRY := ghcr.io/volcano-sh     # Default container registry\n446: DOCKER_TAG := latest                       # Default image tag\n447: VERSION := $(shell git describe --tags --always --dirty 2>/dev/null || echo \"dev\")\n448: COMMIT_SHA := $(shell git rev-parse --short HEAD 2>/dev/null || echo \"unknown\")\n449: \n450: # Image names (constructed)\n451: WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/workloadmanager\n452: ROUTER_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/router\n453: PICOD_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/picod\n454: ```\n455: \n456: ---\n457: \n458: ## File Structure\n459: \n460: ```\n461: project-root/\n462: ├── Makefile                              # Main Makefile with all targets\n463: ├── deployment/\n464: │   └── docker/\n465: │       ├── Dockerfile                    # Workload Manager Dockerfile (AR-032)\n466: │       ├── Dockerfile.router             # Router Dockerfile (AR-032)\n467: │       ├── Dockerfile.picod              # Picod Dockerfile (AR-032)\n468: │       └── test/\n469: │           ├── validate.sh               # Image validation script (new)\n470: │           ├── build_test.sh             # Build test script (new)\n471: │           └── runtime_test.sh           # Runtime test script (new)\n472: ```\n473: \n474: ---\n475: \n476: ## Make Targets\n477: \n478: | Target | Category | Description |\n479: |--------|----------|-------------|\n480: | `docker-build-all` | Build | Build all three Docker images |\n481: | `docker-build-workloadmanager` | Build | Build Workload Manager image |\n482: | `docker-build-router` | Build | Build Router image |\n483: | `docker-build-picod` | Build | Build Picod image |\n484: | `docker-push-all` | Push | Push all images to registry |\n485: | `docker-push-workloadmanager` | Push | Push Workload Manager image |\n486: | `docker-push-router` | Push | Push Router image |\n487: | `docker-push-picod` | Push | Push Picod image |\n488: | `kind-load-all` | Kind | Load all images to Kind cluster |\n489: | `kind-load-workloadmanager` | Kind | Load Workload Manager image to Kind |\n490: | `kind-load-router` | Kind | Load Router image to Kind |\n491: | `kind-load-picod` | Kind | Load Picod image to Kind |\n492: | `docker-buildx-all` | Buildx | Build multi-arch images (amd64, arm64) |\n493: | `docker-buildx-workloadmanager` | Buildx | Build multi-arch Workload Manager |\n494: | `docker-buildx-router` | Buildx | Build multi-arch Router |\n495: | `docker-buildx-picod` | Buildx | Build multi-arch Picod |\n496: | `docker-validate` | Validate | Validate all images |\n497: | `docker-validate-workloadmanager` | Validate | Validate Workload Manager image |\n498: | `docker-validate-router` | Validate | Validate Router image |\n499: | `docker-validate-picod` | Validate | Validate Picod image |\n500: | `docker-test` | Test | Run all Docker tests |\n501: | `docker-test-build` | Test | Run build tests |\n502: | `docker-test-runtime` | Test | Run runtime tests |\n503: | `docker-clean` | Clean | Clean up local images |\n504: | `help` | Help | Print available targets and variables |\n505: \n506: ---\n507: \n508: ## Environment Variables\n509: \n510: | Variable | Purpose | Default | Overridable |\n511: |----------|---------|---------|-------------|\n512: | `DOCKER_REGISTRY` | Container registry URL | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh` | Yes |\n513: | `DOCKER_TAG` | Default image tag | `latest` | Yes |\n514: | `VERSION` | Git-derived version | `git describe` or `dev` | Yes |\n515: | `COMMIT_SHA` | Git commit short hash | `git rev-parse` or `unknown` | Yes |\n516: | `TEST_IMAGE` | Test image for runtime tests | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager:latest` | Yes |\n517: \n518: ---\n519: \n520: ## Script Interfaces\n521: \n522: ### validate.sh\n523: \n524: ```bash\n525: # Usage\n526: ./deployment/docker/test/validate.sh <image-name>\n527: \n528: # Exit codes\n529: 0 - All validations passed\n530: 1 - Validation failed or image not found\n531: \n532: # Validations performed\n533: - Image existence check\n534: - Image size < 50MB\n535: - Layer count <= 5\n536: - Non-root user specified\n537: - Port 8080 exposed\n538: - Health check configured\n539: ```\n540: \n541: ### build_test.sh\n542: \n543: ```bash\n544: # Usage\n545: ./deployment/docker/test/build_test.sh\n546: \n547: # Exit codes\n548: 0 - All build tests passed\n549: 1 - Test failed\n550: \n551: # Tests performed\n552: - Dockerfile existence check (3 files)\n553: - Makefile target availability\n554: - Docker daemon running check\n555: - Docker buildx availability (optional)\n556: ```\n557: \n558: ### runtime_test.sh\n559: \n560: ```bash\n561: # Usage\n562: ./deployment/docker/test/runtime_test.sh\n563: \n564: # Exit codes\n565: 0 - All runtime tests completed\n566: 1 - Critical test failed\n567: \n568: # Tests performed\n569: - Container startup test\n570: - Health check configuration check\n571: - Port exposure check\n572: - Non-root user check\n573: ```\n574: \n575: ---\n576: \n577: ## Acceptance Checklist\n578: \n579: - [ ] `Makefile` — Contains all build, push, kind, buildx, validate, test, clean, and help targets\n580: - [ ] `Makefile` — All targets declared as `.PHONY`\n581: - [ ] `Makefile` — Variables `DOCKER_REGISTRY`, `DOCKER_TAG`, `VERSION`, `COMMIT_SHA` defined\n582: - [ ] `Makefile` — Image name variables for all three components\n583: - [ ] `make help` — Prints all available targets and current variable values\n584: - [ ] `make docker-build-all` — Builds all three images successfully\n585: - [ ] `make docker-push-all` — Pushes all images (with valid credentials)\n586: - [ ] `make kind-load-all` — Loads images to Kind cluster (with Kind installed)\n587: - [ ] `make docker-buildx-all` — Builds multi-arch images (with buildx available)\n588: - [ ] `make docker-validate` — Validates all images\n589: - [ ] `make docker-test` — Runs all tests\n590: - [ ] `make docker-clean` — Cleans up local images\n591: - [ ] `deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` — Exists and is executable\n592: - [ ] `deployment/docker/test/build_test.sh` — Exists and is executable\n593: - [ ] `deployment/docker/test/runtime_test.sh` — Exists and is executable\n594: - [ ] `validate.sh` — Checks image size, layers, user, ports, healthcheck\n595: - [ ] `build_test.sh` — Checks Dockerfiles, Makefile targets, Docker daemon\n596: - [ ] `runtime_test.sh` — Tests container runtime behavior\n597: - [ ] VERSION variable — Derived from git tags with fallback to `dev`\n598: - [ ] COMMIT_SHA variable — Derived from git with fallback to `unknown`\n599: - [ ] Variables overridable — Can be set from environment or command line\n600: - [ ] Error handling — Clean target ignores missing images gracefully\n601: \n602: ---\n603: \n604: ## Open Questions\n605: \n606: 1. Should Windows support be added via PowerShell scripts or WSL-only?\n607: 2. Should cosign image signing be integrated into push targets?\n608: 3. Should remote Docker daemon support (DOCKER_HOST) be explicitly documented?\n609: 4. Should additional validation checks be added (e.g., vulnerability scanning with Trivy)?\n610: 5. Should a `make ci` target be added that chains test → build → validate?\n\n(End of file - total 610 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification — AR-033: Makefile 构建目标体系\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `root`  \n**Language:** Makefile  \n**Size:** M  \n**Type:** Makefile target system for Docker image build, push, validate, test lifecycle management\n\n**Base Specs:** design.md, deployment/docker/delta-spec.md (AR-032)\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-033.1: Build Targets (docker-build-*)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide Make targets for building Docker images for all components (Workload Manager, Router, Picod).\n\n#### Scenario: Build all images","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-033/spec/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775883092867,"end":1775883092905}}}}
