{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775883105732,"sessionID":"ses_2851eb022ffeUsBkCblQKTFCRz","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae1b5c2001wWfsivEI2oyUJP","messageID":"msg_d7ae1af43001LNcOvBrofnc4du","sessionID":"ses_2851eb022ffeUsBkCblQKTFCRz","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883218219,"sessionID":"ses_2851eb022ffeUsBkCblQKTFCRz","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae1b977001qEYamLxaNLFuOb","messageID":"msg_d7ae1af43001LNcOvBrofnc4du","sessionID":"ses_2851eb022ffeUsBkCblQKTFCRz","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_1b9d154aba074356ba2ef21e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-034/spec/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Specification — AR-034: CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 Workflows)\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `.github/workflows`  \n**Language:** YAML  \n**Size:** L  \n**Type:** GitHub Actions workflows for CI/CD automation (build, lint, test, e2e, codegen, copyright, codespell, release, approval)\n\n**Base Specs:** ci-cd/design.md, ci-cd/spec.md\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-034.1: Agentcube CI Workflow (main.yml)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that builds the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.\n\n#### Scenario: PR triggers workflow\n- **GIVEN** a pull request is opened or updated targeting `main` or `release-*`\n- **WHEN** the PR event occurs\n- **THEN** the \"Agentcube CI Workflow\" SHALL be triggered\n\n#### Scenario: Checkout repository\n- **GIVEN** workflow is running\n- **WHEN** the job starts\n- **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository code\n\n#### Scenario: Setup Docker Buildx\n- **GIVEN** repository is checked out\n- **WHEN** job continues\n- **THEN** it SHALL set up Docker Buildx\n\n#### Scenario: Verify Docker availability\n- **GIVEN** Docker Buildx is set up\n- **WHEN** job continues\n- **THEN** it SHALL verify `docker` and `buildx` versions\n\n#### Scenario: Execute docker-build\n- **GIVEN** Docker is available\n- **WHEN** build step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute `make docker-build`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-034.2: E2E Tests Workflow (e2e.yml)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that runs end-to-end tests on Kind Kubernetes cluster for pull requests to `main` or `release-*` branches.\n\n#### Scenario: PR triggers e2e workflow\n- **GIVEN** a pull request is opened or updated targeting `main` or `release-*`\n- **WHEN** the PR event occurs\n- **THEN** the \"Agentcube E2E Tests\" workflow SHALL be triggered\n\n#### Scenario: Setup Go environment\n- **GIVEN** workflow is running\n- **WHEN** the job starts\n- **THEN** it SHALL set up Go version 1.23\n\n#### Scenario: Install Kind cluster\n- **GIVEN** Go is ready\n- **WHEN** Kind action runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL install Kind v0.30.0 with `install_only: true` and cluster name `agentcube-e2e`\n\n#### Scenario: Set artifacts path\n- **GIVEN** Kind is installed\n- **WHEN** environment is configured\n- **THEN** `ARTIFACTS_PATH` SHALL be set to `${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`\n\n#### Scenario: Run e2e tests\n- **GIVEN** cluster is ready\n- **WHEN** test step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute `make e2e`\n\n#### Scenario: Upload failure logs\n- **GIVEN** e2e tests fail\n- **WHEN** failure occurs\n- **THEN** it SHALL upload `e2e-logs/` directory as artifact\n\n#### Scenario: Clean up cluster\n- **GIVEN** tests complete (pass or fail)\n- **WHEN** job finishes\n- **THEN** it SHALL always run `make e2e-clean`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-034.3: Lint Workflow (lint.yml)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that runs `golangci-lint` when Go-related paths change on pull requests to `main` or `release-*`.\n\n#### Scenario: PR triggers lint workflow\n- **GIVEN** a pull request targets `main` or `release-*`\n- **WHEN** the PR event occurs\n- **THEN** the \"Lint\" workflow SHALL be triggered\n\n#### Scenario: Path filter for Go files\n- **GIVEN** workflow is running\n- **WHEN** paths-filter action runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL match `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, or `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n\n#### Scenario: Setup Go for linting\n- **GIVEN** path filter indicates changes\n- **WHEN** lint job continues\n- **THEN** it SHALL set up Go version 1.24\n\n#### Scenario: Run golangci-lint\n- **GIVEN** Go is ready\n- **WHEN** lint step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute `make lint`\n\n#### Scenario: No Go changes\n- **GIVEN** path filter indicates no Go-related changes\n- **WHEN** workflow runs\n- **THEN** lint step SHALL be skipped\n\n---\n\n### REQ-034.4: Python SDK Tests Workflow (python-sdk-tests.yml)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that runs pytest for the Python SDK when `sdk-python/**` paths change.\n\n#### Scenario: PR triggers Python SDK workflow\n- **GIVEN** a pull request or merge_group event occurs\n- **WHEN** the event targets the repository\n- **THEN** the \"Python SDK Tests\" workflow SHALL be triggered\n\n#### Scenario: Path filter for SDK files\n- **GIVEN** workflow is running\n- **WHEN** paths-filter action runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL match `sdk-python/**`\n\n#### Scenario: Setup Python environment\n- **GIVEN** path filter indicates SDK changes\n- **WHEN** job continues\n- **THEN** it SHALL set up Python 3.12 with working directory `sdk-python`\n\n#### Scenario: Install pytest\n- **GIVEN** Python is ready\n- **WHEN** dependency step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute `pip install pytest`\n\n#### Scenario: Install SDK in editable mode\n- **GIVEN** pytest is installed\n- **WHEN** install step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute `pip install -e .`\n\n#### Scenario: Run pytest\n- **GIVEN** SDK is installed\n- **WHEN** test step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute `python -m pytest tests/ -v`\n\n#### Scenario: No SDK changes\n- **GIVEN** path filter indicates no SDK changes\n- **WHEN** workflow runs\n- **THEN** test steps SHALL be skipped\n\n---\n\n### REQ-034.5: Python Lint Workflow (python-lint.yml)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that runs Ruff linting when Python-related paths change.\n\n#### Scenario: PR triggers Python lint workflow\n- **GIVEN** a pull request targets `main` or `release-*`\n- **WHEN** the PR event occurs\n- **THEN** the \"Python Lint\" workflow SHALL be triggered\n\n#### Scenario: Path filter for Python files\n- **GIVEN** workflow is running\n- **WHEN** paths-filter action runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL match `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, or the workflow file itself\n\n#### Scenario: Setup Python for linting\n- **GIVEN** path filter indicates changes\n- **WHEN** job continues\n- **THEN** it SHALL set up Python 3.10\n\n#### Scenario: Install Ruff\n- **GIVEN** Python is ready\n- **WHEN** dependency step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute `pip install ruff`\n\n#### Scenario: Run Ruff check\n- **GIVEN** Ruff is installed\n- **WHEN** lint step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute `python3 -m ruff check . --config pyproject.toml`\n\n#### Scenario: No Python changes\n- **GIVEN** path filter indicates no Python-related changes\n- **WHEN** workflow runs\n- **THEN** lint steps SHALL be skipped\n\n---\n\n### REQ-034.6: Test Coverage Workflow (test-coverage.yml)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that runs race-enabled Go tests with coverage reporting on `pkg/...` for pull requests, merge groups, or workflow calls.\n\n#### Scenario: Multiple triggers for coverage\n- **GIVEN** a `pull_request`, `merge_group`, or `workflow_call` event occurs\n- **WHEN** the event targets the repository\n- **THEN** the \"Test Coverage\" workflow SHALL be triggered\n\n#### Scenario: Path filter for coverage\n- **GIVEN** workflow is running\n- **WHEN** paths-filter action runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL match `**` excluding `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`\n\n#### Scenario: Free disk space\n- **GIVEN** path filter indicates changes\n- **WHEN** job starts\n- **THEN** it SHALL free disk space on the runner\n\n#### Scenario: Setup Go for tests\n- **GIVEN** disk space is ready\n- **WHEN** job continues\n- **THEN** it SHALL set up Go version 1.24\n\n#### Scenario: Run Go tests with coverage\n- **GIVEN** Go is ready\n- **WHEN** test step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...`\n\n#### Scenario: Upload coverage to Codecov\n- **GIVEN** coverage report is generated\n- **WHEN** upload step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL upload `coverage.out` to Codecov (using `secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN` if available)\n\n#### Scenario: Upload coverage artifact\n- **GIVEN** coverage report exists\n- **WHEN** artifact step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL upload `go-coverage` artifact\n\n#### Scenario: Write to step summary\n- **GIVEN** tests complete\n- **WHEN** summary step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL write coverage results to GitHub step summary\n\n---\n\n### REQ-034.7: Codegen Check Workflow (codegen-check.yml)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that verifies generated artifacts match `make gen-all` when API, hack, workflow, or Makefile inputs change.\n\n#### Scenario: PR triggers codegen workflow\n- **GIVEN** a pull request targets `main` or `release-*`\n- **WHEN** the PR event occurs\n- **THEN** the \"Codegen Check\" workflow SHALL be triggered\n\n#### Scenario: Path filter for codegen\n- **GIVEN** workflow is running\n- **WHEN** paths-filter action runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL match `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, or `Makefile`\n\n#### Scenario: Setup Go for codegen\n- **GIVEN** path filter indicates changes\n- **WHEN** job continues\n- **THEN** it SHALL set up Go version 1.24.4\n\n#### Scenario: Run gen-check\n- **GIVEN** Go is ready\n- **WHEN** check step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute `make gen-check` (runs `gen-all` then `git diff --exit-code`)\n\n#### Scenario: Generated code out of date\n- **GIVEN** `make gen-all` produces changes\n- **WHEN** `git diff --exit-code` runs\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL fail indicating generated code is stale\n\n#### Scenario: No codegen-related changes\n- **GIVEN** path filter indicates no relevant changes\n- **WHEN** workflow runs\n- **THEN** check steps SHALL be skipped\n\n---\n\n### REQ-034.8: Copyright Check Workflow (copyright-check.yml)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that ensures `make gen-copyright` produces no git diff when applicable files change.\n\n#### Scenario: PR triggers copyright workflow\n- **GIVEN** a pull request targets `main` or `release-*`\n- **WHEN** the PR event occurs\n- **THEN** the \"Copyright Check\" workflow SHALL be triggered\n\n#### Scenario: Path filter for copyright\n- **GIVEN** workflow is running\n- **WHEN** paths-filter action runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL match all files excluding `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**`\n\n#### Scenario: Install moreutils\n- **GIVEN** path filter indicates changes\n- **WHEN** job starts\n- **THEN** it SHALL install `moreutils` package (for `sponge` command)\n\n#### Scenario: Run gen-copyright\n- **GIVEN** moreutils is installed\n- **WHEN** generate step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute `make gen-copyright`\n\n#### Scenario: Verify no diff\n- **GIVEN** copyright headers are generated\n- **WHEN** diff step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute `git diff --exit-code`\n\n#### Scenario: Copyright headers missing\n- **GIVEN** files lack proper copyright headers\n- **WHEN** `git diff --exit-code` runs\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL fail indicating missing copyright headers\n\n#### Scenario: No copyright-relevant changes\n- **GIVEN** path filter indicates no relevant changes\n- **WHEN** workflow runs\n- **THEN** check steps SHALL be skipped\n\n---\n\n### REQ-034.9: Codespell Workflow (codespell.yml)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that runs codespell spell-checking on pull requests to `main` or `release-*` branches.\n\n#### Scenario: PR triggers codespell workflow\n- **GIVEN** a pull request targets `main` or `release-*`\n- **WHEN** the PR event occurs\n- **THEN** the \"Codespell\" workflow SHALL be triggered\n\n#### Scenario: Backup problematic files\n- **GIVEN** workflow is running\n- **WHEN** job starts\n- **THEN** it SHALL backup and remove `pyproject.toml`, `package.json`, `package-lock.json` at repo root and nested copies\n\n#### Scenario: Install codespell\n- **GIVEN** files are backed up\n- **WHEN** dependency step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute `pip install codespell`\n\n#### Scenario: Run codespell\n- **GIVEN** codespell is installed\n- **WHEN** spell check step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL run `codespell --check-filenames --skip <globs> --ignore-words-list fo,nam,te,notin,NotIn .`\n\n#### Scenario: Restore backed-up files\n- **GIVEN** codespell completes\n- **WHEN** cleanup step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL restore all backed-up files\n\n#### Scenario: Spelling errors found\n- **GIVEN** repository contains misspellings\n- **WHEN** codespell runs\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL fail with list of misspelled words\n\n---\n\n### REQ-034.10: Build and Push Release Images Workflow (build-push-release.yml)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that builds and pushes multi-architecture images for workloadmanager, router, and picod to GitHub Container Registry on pushes to `main` and semantic version tags.\n\n#### Scenario: Push to main triggers workflow\n- **GIVEN** a push to `main` branch occurs\n- **WHEN** the push event completes\n- **THEN** the \"Build and Push Release Images\" workflow SHALL be triggered\n\n#### Scenario: Tag push triggers workflow\n- **GIVEN** a push of tag matching `v*.*.*` or `v*.*.*-*` occurs\n- **WHEN** the tag event completes\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL be triggered\n\n#### Scenario: Determine image tag from ref\n- **GIVEN** workflow is running\n- **WHEN** `TAG` environment variable is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `github.ref_name` if tag, otherwise `latest`\n\n#### Scenario: Setup Go for build\n- **GIVEN** workflow is triggered\n- **WHEN** job starts\n- **THEN** it SHALL set up Go version 1.24.4\n\n#### Scenario: Setup Docker Buildx\n- **GIVEN** Go is ready\n- **WHEN** job continues\n- **THEN** it SHALL set up Docker Buildx\n\n#### Scenario: Login to GHCR\n- **GIVEN** Buildx is ready\n- **WHEN** login step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL authenticate to `ghcr.io` using `GITHUB_TOKEN`\n\n#### Scenario: Build and push workloadmanager\n- **GIVEN** registry login succeeds\n- **WHEN** build step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute `make docker-buildx-push` with `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` and `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE=workloadmanager:${TAG}`\n\n#### Scenario: Build and push router\n- **GIVEN** workflow is running\n- **WHEN** router build step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute `make docker-buildx-push-router` with appropriate image variables\n\n#### Scenario: Build and push picod\n- **GIVEN** workflow is running\n- **WHEN** picod build step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute `make docker-buildx-push-picod` with appropriate image variables\n\n#### Scenario: Multi-architecture build\n- **GIVEN** buildx is available\n- **WHEN** build commands run\n- **THEN** images SHALL be built for `linux/amd64,linux/arm64` platforms\n\n---\n\n### REQ-034.11: Dify Plugin Publish Workflow (dify-plugin-publish.yml)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that publishes the Dify plugin to the `langgenius/dify-plugins` repository when `dify-plugin/v*` tags are pushed.\n\n#### Scenario: Dify plugin tag triggers workflow\n- **GIVEN** a push of tag matching `dify-plugin/v*` occurs\n- **WHEN** the tag event completes\n- **THEN** the \"Dify Plugin Publish\" workflow SHALL be triggered\n\n#### Scenario: Download dify-plugin CLI\n- **GIVEN** workflow is running\n- **WHEN** setup step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL download `dify-plugin` CLI version 0.0.6\n\n#### Scenario: Install yq processor\n- **GIVEN** workflow continues\n- **WHEN** tooling step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL install `yq` YAML processor\n\n#### Scenario: Read manifest\n- **GIVEN** tools are ready\n- **WHEN** manifest step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL read `manifest.yaml` for plugin metadata\n\n#### Scenario: Package plugin\n- **GIVEN** manifest is parsed\n- **WHEN** packaging step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL package the Dify plugin\n\n#### Scenario: Checkout plugins repository\n- **GIVEN** plugin is packaged\n- **WHEN** repository step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL checkout `author/dify-plugins` using token authentication\n\n#### Scenario: Move plugin to repository\n- **GIVEN** repository is checked out\n- **WHEN** file step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL move `.difypkg` file to appropriate location\n\n#### Scenario: Create pull request\n- **GIVEN** plugin files are staged\n- **WHEN** PR step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL create branch, commit, push, and create PR to `langgenius/dify-plugins` using `gh pr create` with `GH_TOKEN`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-034.12: Approve Workflows Workflow (workflows-approve.yml)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a GitHub Actions workflow that optionally approves pending workflow runs for pull requests from repeat contributors or those labeled `ok-to-test`.\n\n#### Scenario: PR target triggers approval workflow\n- **GIVEN** a `pull_request_target` event with types `labeled` or `synchronize` targets `main` or `release-**`\n- **WHEN** the event occurs\n- **THEN** the \"Approve Workflows\" workflow SHALL be triggered\n\n#### Scenario: Check contributor PR history\n- **GIVEN** workflow is running\n- **WHEN** github-script step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL list contributor's PRs to determine if first-time\n\n#### Scenario: Check for ok-to-test label\n- **GIVEN** workflow is running\n- **WHEN** label check runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL check if PR has `ok-to-test` label\n\n#### Scenario: Approve for repeat contributor\n- **GIVEN** contributor has more than one PR\n- **WHEN** approval logic runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL list workflow runs with `status: action_required` for the head SHA and approve each\n\n#### Scenario: Approve for labeled PR\n- **GIVEN** PR has `ok-to-test` label\n- **WHEN** approval logic runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL list workflow runs with `status: action_required` for the head SHA and approve each\n\n#### Scenario: Skip for first-time contributor\n- **GIVEN** contributor has only one PR and no `ok-to-test` label\n- **WHEN** approval logic runs\n- **THEN** no workflow runs SHALL be approved\n\n---\n\n## Data Types\n\n```yaml\n# Workflow trigger types\non:\n  pull_request:\n    branches: [main, release-*]\n  pull_request_target:\n    branches: [main, release-**]\n    types: [labeled, synchronize]\n  push:\n    branches: [main]\n    tags: ['v*.*.*', 'v*.*.*-*', 'dify-plugin/v*']\n  merge_group:\n  workflow_call:\n\n# Common job environment variables\nenv:\n  TAG: ${{ github.ref_type == 'tag' && github.ref_name || 'latest' }}\n  IMAGE_REGISTRY: ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}\n  ARTIFACTS_PATH: ${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs\n```\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\n.github/\n└── workflows/\n    ├── main.yml                      # Agentcube CI Workflow (REQ-034.1)\n    ├── e2e.yml                       # Agentcube E2E Tests (REQ-034.2)\n    ├── lint.yml                      # Lint (REQ-034.3)\n    ├── python-sdk-tests.yml          # Python SDK Tests (REQ-034.4)\n    ├── python-lint.yml               # Python Lint (REQ-034.5)\n    ├── test-coverage.yml             # Test Coverage (REQ-034.6)\n    ├── codegen-check.yml             # Codegen Check (REQ-034.7)\n    ├── copyright-check.yml           # Copyright Check (REQ-034.8)\n    ├── codespell.yml                 # Codespell (REQ-034.9)\n    ├── build-push-release.yml        # Build and Push Release Images (REQ-034.10)\n    ├── dify-plugin-publish.yml       # Dify Plugin Publish (REQ-034.11)\n    └── workflows-approve.yml         # Approve Workflows (REQ-034.12)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Workflows Summary\n\n| Workflow | File | Triggers | Path Filters | Key Jobs |\n|----------|------|----------|--------------|----------|\n| Agentcube CI Workflow | main.yml | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | None | build |\n| Agentcube E2E Tests | e2e.yml | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | None | e2e-test |\n| Lint | lint.yml | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | Go files | golangci |\n| Python SDK Tests | python-sdk-tests.yml | `pull_request`, `merge_group` | `sdk-python/**` | python-sdk-tests |\n| Python Lint | python-lint.yml | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | Python files | python_lint |\n| Test Coverage | test-coverage.yml | `pull_request`, `merge_group`, `workflow_call` | All except media | coverage |\n| Codegen Check | codegen-check.yml | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | API/hack/workflow/Makefile | codegen-check |\n| Copyright Check | copyright-check.yml | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | Code files only | build |\n| Codespell | codespell.yml | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | None (tree scan) | codespell |\n| Build and Push Release | build-push-release.yml | `push` → `main`, tags `v*` | None | build-and-push |\n| Dify Plugin Publish | dify-plugin-publish.yml | `push` tags `dify-plugin/v*` | None | publish |\n| Approve Workflows | workflows-approve.yml | `pull_request_target` → `main` | None | approve |\n\n---\n\n## Secrets and Credentials\n\n| Secret | Purpose | Used By |\n|--------|---------|---------|\n| `secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN` | Codecov coverage upload | test-coverage.yml (optional) |\n| `secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN` | GHCR registry login, cross-repo PR | build-push-release.yml, dify-plugin-publish.yml, workflows-approve.yml |\n| `secrets.PLUGIN_ACTION` | Dify plugin repository checkout and PR | dify-plugin-publish.yml |\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Checklist\n\n- [ ] `main.yml` — Triggers on PR to `main`/`release-*`, runs `make docker-build`\n- [ ] `e2e.yml` — Triggers on PR, sets up Kind v0.30.0, runs `make e2e`, uploads logs on failure, cleans up\n- [ ] `lint.yml` — Path-filtered for Go files, runs `make lint` with Go 1.24\n- [ ] `python-sdk-tests.yml` — Path-filtered for `sdk-python/**`, runs pytest with Python 3.12\n- [ ] `python-lint.yml` — Path-filtered for Python files, runs Ruff with Python 3.10\n- [ ] `test-coverage.yml` — Runs `go test -race` with coverage, uploads to Codecov\n- [ ] `codegen-check.yml` — Path-filtered, runs `make gen-check` with Go 1.24.4\n- [ ] `copyright-check.yml` — Installs moreutils, runs `make gen-copyright`, checks diff\n- [ ] `codespell.yml` — Backups files, runs codespell with ignore list, restores files\n- [ ] `build-push-release.yml` — Triggers on push to `main`/tags, builds multi-arch, pushes to GHCR\n- [ ] `dify-plugin-publish.yml` — Triggers on `dify-plugin/v*` tags, creates PR to `langgenius/dify-plugins`\n- [ ] `workflows-approve.yml` — Approves workflows for repeat contributors or `ok-to-test` labeled PRs\n- [ ] All workflows — Use appropriate Go/Python versions as specified\n- [ ] All workflows — Have correct path filters configured\n- [ ] All workflows — Handle skip conditions correctly when paths don't match\n- [ ] Secrets — CODECOV_TOKEN is optional in test-coverage.yml\n- [ ] Secrets — GITHUB_TOKEN used for GHCR login and cross-repo operations\n- [ ] E2E workflow — Uses Kind action with `install_only: true`\n- [ ] Release workflow — Correctly determines TAG from ref type\n\n---\n\n## Open Questions\n\n1. Should Windows CI runners be added for cross-platform validation?\n2. Should SLSA/SBOM generation be integrated into the release workflow?\n3. Should Dependabot be configured alongside these workflows?\n4. Should workflow concurrency limits be added to prevent queue buildup?\n5. Should additional notification hooks (Slack, Discord) be added for release failures?\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-034/spec/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-034/spec/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775883218199,"end":1775883218214}}}}
